Note: core-cpu1 subsequently aborts during its own process-exit path
("libgcc_s.so.1 must be installed for pthread_cancel to work") — this
occurs AFTER PIXXEL_MAIN has already printed [PASS] and called
CFE_ES_ExitApp, and is a target-image runtime-dependency gap (missing
libgcc_s.so.1 package in the minimal rootfs), not a defect in the driver
or the two Pixxel apps. Fix: add libgcc to IMAGE_INSTALL, or RDEPENDS
the pixxel-apps package on it.
